node.text: Sound up! Time for a second installment of magic sunny times by, and in, the Tiddy. Takes us right back. To watch the full video, head to the link in our bio. This snippet features @msmirandasawyer @officiallymaitlis @aldousharding @lukewrightpoet & lots more!

📣 SOUND ON! 📣 We're leaving you now with our film of the last festival. Link in bio for the full length version.

We hope it will lift you up and drop you down on our corner of South East Cornwall, shaking some memories on the way. From the beginning, Port Eliot Festival has existed purely for its own sake – to create moments and situations that are inspirational and make people happy. It's been an annual invitation to be part of a movement of enjoyment and we are determined to be back one day. If we ever have something exciting to report, we'll be back and shouting about it. Thank you, everyone.

Sound on!

A few of you told us you missed out on our 2019 merch, so we've put tees and totes back on sale for a short time only. Available until the end of October at porteliotfestival.com/shop - and we've also extended the pre-order on prints until midday next Weds.
Last last last last last chance to get one of these utterly excellent posters hand-screenprinted by @rosie1ea. We're taking pre-orders up until Wednesday next week. porteliotfestival.com/shop 🐘
Peeping through! 🌿 We must have drained the last of the Summer sunshine (along with the wine) that weekend. #whathappenedtosummer #itwasworthitthough

Three big cheers for the cap'ns of this fine ship - our most excellent trio of Directors, @colinbookshaped, @popshandy & @louis_eliot!

Our hexagonal hedge maze. Bet it's seen some things. One year, this sat next door to a cinema curated by @martinscorsese_ and we're still pinching ourselves about that. #ifthesehedgescouldtalk

Pure messy glee! We so loved having @thejoyjournal here in Wildlings Wood, connecting little ones with nature through art, with natural paints and materials. And look at all the grins. It works. 🌾🍂
.
.
And no better time to say, huge props to Grace, the brilliant producer of Wildlings Wood (and many other things here at Port!). It was filled with mischief, laughter and play all weekend. ♡
One of our absolute highlights of this year's festival (and one of the best things we've seen all year / ever): the inimitable @dakhabrakha on the Park. #dancelikeadervish

The @woodfiredcanteen long table suppers were a bit good, eh wot? That view over the estuary! Swipe for sights of our well-dressed diners and evidence that our tables were, as advertised, extremely long. You could probably see them from space an' all. Photos by @louisearoberts & the scene from above courtesy of @phasefoto.

Ehem... Did anyone find themselves being chided on the lawn by this gaggle of nuns? Mother Superior was only too pleased to help redeem sinners. Photo taken by @Tommy_Hatwell who, we're told, takes a better picture after a good whipping.
GIGANTIC congratulations to Jen and Andy Hopper who were married at the boathouse at this year's festival! ♥️♥️♥️

You're all our mates. Spot yourselves in this year's beautiful gallery, curated by @louisearoberts - link in biog.⚡

PLEASE BE UPSTANDING FOR THE TEAM! Port Eliot Festival could be many things, but this unique blend of people make a special sort of magic happen. A huge, great big round of applause to all of these brilliant people (and the few who are missing here). Special big ups to our Directors Louis, Colin and Poppy. Photo by @benjaminpryor 💙

We have nothing but love for you lot. Thank you for joining us for one last big (ENORMOUS) hoorah. That might have been our best ever, and it hasn't really sunk in that we're wrapping up, so let's just gaze at this year's Tiddy-side photos and transport ourselves back. We've got lots more for you. Best moments? Funny stories? Go on, share 'em below.
Port Eliot looking beautiful by dusk 🌖
The Open Fire stage has been flaming brilliant all weekend, not least an audience with cocktail connoisseur and Port Eliot regular @jackabevan. Photos by the excellent @benjaminpryor.

Friday was spesh. @daisylowe's Wildlings Wood storytelling set, @audiobookshq and an Alice in Wonderland treasure hunt amongst the highlights. Set for an excellent Saturday with @lilyallen and @russellbrand's storytelling set in Wildlings Wood, 6pm... Tickets on the door!
Suspended on the banks of the Tiddy. Bustling down by the river today! Get down here. Tickets on the gate.

And we are go! A storming Thursday with @aldousharding in @caughtbytheriver, amongst many other wonders around the grounds. The weather's balmy and breezy in Cornwall, so if you're sweating in the city, come and join us for an estuary swim. Tickets on the gate. #PortEliot2019

IT'S TOMORROW! Both day and weekend tickets available online or on the gate. NB we don't sell Thursday day tickets - @aldousharding, @pipblom (+ more) are a special added bonus for those joining for the weekend! 🥂🌴
